def: To shoot out the nose or toss it in the air; Crabb.
The state or quality of being peccable; lability to sin.The common peccability of mankind. Dr. H. More.
Originally, work done by the day; work done by a journeyman athis trade.
To drive from a house or habitation; to dislodge; hence, todeprive of shelter.
Of or pertaining to the middle of the ethmoid region or ethmoidbone.-- n. (Anat.)
A drain trench, in a ditch or moat; -- called also cuvette.
In a tight manner; closely; nearly.
History of the evolution of forms; that part of ontogeny thatdeals with the germ history of forms; -- distinguished fromphysiogeny. Haeckel.
One who holds to the atomic philosophy or theory. Locke.
